						               													<description>This card game is played mainly in Afganistan and Iran. It was mentioned in an article in GAMES magazine, sometime in the 2000s. It is similar to, but differs a fair bit (scoring and key cards), from the card game known as Casino and another called &amp;quot;Bazra&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game uses a standard 52-card deck, without jokers. After an initial deal of five cards to each person (2-player only), two cards are turned up in the middle of the table. After playing one card at a time from the hand, another 5 cards are dealt to the players once their current hand is empty. Thus, each game segment lasts 5 rounds (10 cards per round + the initial 2 card outlay).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Points (always 5 per game segment) are given at the end of the deck for the following:&amp;#10;Most cards = 2&amp;#10;Most clubs = 1&amp;#10;2 of clubs = 1&amp;#10;10 of diamonds = 1&amp;#10;&amp;#10;See the A new 2-player card game (for most of you) for a visual explanation of rules and scoring basics.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
